dmca.title: Scientologists Dislike the Truthaboutscientology.com
dmca.body:
From: [Private]
Message-ID: [Private]
Date: Fri, 30 Sep 2005 19:58:32 EDT
Subject: Unauthorized Use of Copyrighted Materials 
To: abuse@npsis.com
CC: abuse@support.eli.net, [Private]

Dear Abuse:

     Our office represents a number of Churches of Scientology concerning
intellectual property matters, including but not limited to Church of Scientology Western
United States, Church of Scientology Celebrity Centre International, Church of
Scientology Flag Ship Service Organization, Church of Scientology Flag Service Organization.  Our clients are owners of the copyrights to a number of magazines which include, but are not limited to, Advance; Celebrity; Freewinds; and Source.

     We have written to you in the past concerning your subscriber, Ms. Kristi
Wachter.  She has placed an enormous number of our clients' copyrighted works
noted above on her webpage on NPSIS's website without the authorization of our client. 
The URLs are so numerous (making up nearly 15 pages of URLs, single-spaced) that I
have attached them to this notice. 

     Your subscriber's action in this regard violates United States copyright law. Accordingly, we are asking for your help in removing these copyright infringements from this website.

     I have a good faith belief, and in fact am certain, that the posting of these works through your system was not authorized by my clients, any agent of my clients, or the law.

     I declare under penalty of perjury that this information is accurate and that I am authorized to act on behalf of Church of Scientology Western United States, Church of Scientology Celebrity Centre International, Church of Scientology Flag Ship Service Organization, Church of Scientology Flag Service Organization in this matter.

     I appreciate your help with this matter.

Regards,
[Private]
Moxon & Kobrin
[Private]
Los Angeles, California 90010
Tel: (213) 487-4468
Fax: (213) 487-5385
